<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Scallion Pancakes</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
            <li>3/4 cup boiling water</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons sesame oil</li>
            <li>1 cup thinly sliced scallions (green onions)</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Vegetable oil for frying</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Chinese</li>
            <li>Appetizer</li>
            <li>Crispy</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Place the all-purpose flour in a large bowl. Gradually add the boiling water, stirring continuously until a dough forms.</li>
            <li>Knead the dough on a floured surface until it becomes smooth. Cover and let it rest for 30 minutes.</li>
            <li>Divide the dough into four equal portions. Roll out each portion into a thin circle.</li>
            <li>Brush each circle with sesame oil and sprinkle sliced scallions evenly over the surface. Add salt to taste.</li>
            <li>Roll up each circle into a tight log and then coil each log into a round dough ball.</li>
            <li>Flatten each dough ball into a pancake shape, ensuring the scallions are evenly distributed.</li>
            <li>Heat vegetable oil in a pan over medium-high heat. Fry each pancake until both sides are golden brown and crispy.</li>
            <li>Place the cooked scallion pancakes on a paper towel to absorb excess oil.</li>
            <li>Serve the pancakes warm, sliced into wedges.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your flavorful Scallion Pancakes!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

